  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nOnly when using `truffle test`, I cannot get the initialized parameters such as deploy owner. On the other hand, when deploying the same contract with a migration file and use the deployed JSON file, it is found successfully.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n### test case\r\n```javascript\r\nconst Contract = artifacts.require(\"Contract\")\r\nconst contract = await Contract.new({ 'from': sender })\r\nconst owner = await contract.owner() // is 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Contract.sol\r\n```javascript\r\ncontract Contract is Ownable {\r\n    function initialize() public initializer {\r\n        Ownable.initialize(msg.sender);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nI expect I would get the same address as the sender that I designated when initializing in the test case.\r\n\r\n> const contract = await Contract.new({ 'from': sender })\r\n\r\nI tried another way; \r\n\r\n> const contract = await Contract.deployed({ 'from': sender })\r\n\r\nbut it still fails.\r\n\r\nHowever, when using ehters.js and deployed contract\r\n\r\n> const Contract = new ethers.Contract(xxx,xxx,xxx)\r\n\r\nit works successfully. Got the same address as expected.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\nMac\r\n10.15.4\r\n\r\n\"truffle\": \"^5.1.9\"\r\n\"node\": \"v11.15.0\"\r\n\"npm\":\"v6.7.0\"\r\n\"ganache\": \"v6.8.1\"\r\n",
